# Headless @WebTest — GITHUB_ACTIONS

`WebTestExtension` enables Chrome `--headless` only when `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true` (see `src/test/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/WebTestExtension.java`). GitHub Actions sets this automatically; **local runs must set it explicitly** to match CI and avoid failures when no display is available.

## Always prefix test commands

```bash
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B test -Ptest-web
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw -B verify -Ptest-it -Dcontraponto.smoke.image=contraponto:ci-smoke
GITHUB_ACTIONS=true ./mvnw test -Dtest=SomeWebTest#methodName
```

Use the same prefix for parallel profile runs (`-Ptest-unit`, `-Ptest-quarkus`, `-Ptest-web`, `-Ptest-it`).

Docker-smoke also requires `/etc/hosts` entries — see [`src/test/resources/docker-smoke/README.md`](../../src/test/resources/docker-smoke/README.md).

## Do not

- Run `./mvnw verify` or `./mvnw test` without `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true` when `@WebTest` / `web`-tagged tests are in scope.
- Hard-code `--headless` in test code — the env var is the single switch shared with CI.

## When changing WebTestExtension

Keep the `GITHUB_ACTIONS` gate; document any new Chrome flags in this rule if they affect local vs CI behavior.
